T-Camera Plus S3 (ESP32-S3) — Camera Web Server

This project implements a **live MJPEG streaming web server** for the **LilyGO T-Camera Plus S3 (V1.1)** using the ESP32-S3 Dev Module.  
It allows real-time camera streaming over Wi-Fi and can be viewed from any browser on the same network

Clone the Repository

Clone the official LilyGO board-support repository and navigate to the example:

git clone -b arduino-esp32-libs_V2.0.14 https://github.com/Xinyuan-LilyGO/T-CameraPlus-S3.git
cd T-CameraPlus-S3/examples/Camera_WebServer



Refer to the official LilyGO documentation for the correct pin mappings and board-specific configurations:
Pin Overview — https://github.com/Xinyuan-LilyGO/T-CameraPlus-S3/tree/arduino-esp32-libs_V2.0.14?tab=readme-ov-file#pinoverview
Ensure your pin_config.h corresponds to your hardware version (for example V1.1).


Setting	Value
Board	ESP32S3 Dev Module
Upload Speed	921600
USB Mode	Hardware CDC and JTAG
USB CDC On Boot	Enabled
USB Firmware MSC On Boot	Disabled
USB DFU On Boot	Disabled
CPU Frequency	240MHz (WiFi)
Flash Mode	QIO 80MHz
Flash Size	16MB (128Mb)
Core Debug Level	None
Partition Scheme	16M Flash (3MB APP/9.9MB FATFS)
PSRAM	QSPI PSRAM
Arduino Runs On	Core 1
Events Run On	Core 1
